<TITLE> Telephone disruption in Savar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, April 18 (bdnews24.com)  Nearly 10,000 subscribers with the state-owned BTCL telephone company in Savar upazila have been without a line since Sunday morning. Ahsan Habib Tarafdar, divisional engineer of BTCL said that a fault in a 15 foot fibre optical cable has caused the problem. He told bdnews24.com that they will start restoration of the connection as soon as a fibre optic cable arrives from Dhaka. He also said that they will be able to fix the connection by Sunday evening. bdnews
